      • getPseudoPIPHelper

        public static PseudoPIPHelper getPseudoPIPHelper(PIP pip)
        Gets the pseudo PIP helper for the corresponding PIP. (see also PseudoPIPHelper.getPseudoPIPMap(com.xilinx.rapidwright.device.Device))
        Parameters:
        pip - The existing pseudo PIP of interest.
        Returns:
        The pseudo PIP helper object, or null if none could be found.

      • getPseudoPIPMap

        public static Map<TileTypeEnum,HashMap<PIPWires,PseudoPIPHelper>> getPseudoPIPMap(Device device)
        Gets a map for the given device that enumerates all pseudo PIPs for each tile type. This map is cached so that secondary calls do not regenerate the map.
        Parameters:
        device - The device of interest
        Returns:
        A map of maps where the set of keys are the tile types and values are the maps of abstract PIP (see PIPWires) to their respective pseudo PIP helper class.
